>[Question]
>4 points: A(1.5,2.5)   B(9,16)   C(11.5,20.5)   D(4,7)
>
>When joined, do these points make a parallelogram......
>How to prove it..........
>Thanx,
>Sudharsha
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Check the definition of a parallelogram. Opposite sides have to be 
parallel, so see whether AB and DC are parallel, and whether BC and 
DA are parallel. Use slopes.

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


